SIMPLE: precedency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Precedency
<hw>Pre*ced"en*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧c⟦eacute⟧dence</ets>. See <er>Precede</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or state of preceding or going before in order
of time; priority; <as>as, one event has <ex>precedence</ex> of
another</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act or state of going or being before in rank or
dignity, or the place of honor; right to a more honorable place;
superior rank; <as>as, barons have <ex>precedence</ex> of
commoners</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which of them [the different desires] has the
<qex>precedency</qex> in determining the will to the next action?</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Antecedence; priority; pre⟦eum⟧minence;
preference; superiority.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Precedent</ent>⟦br⟧
